                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.643/79: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-01-05T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 5, 1929—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7. Your 4, January 3, 6 p.m. In regard to matters of official etiquette such as
                    naval honors the Department considers it advisable that henceforth the officers
                    of this Government should accord To Chinese national and provincial authorities
                    the courtesies usually accorded to the authorities of a fully recognized foreign
                    State.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
